FBIS3-20223 "drweu060_p_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Mar 1994 GREECE Spokesman: EU Ministers Statements `Strange' NC2803183494 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 1500 GMT 28 Mar 94 NC2803183494 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Language: Greek Article Type:BFN [Text] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos today described statements made by the European Union [EU] foreign ministers in Ioannina encouraging Skopje's [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia--FYROM] provocativeness as strange. Venizelos called upon the EU foreign ministers to be more careful when making statements so that [FYROM President Kiro] Gligorov does not see them as an encouragement toward his positions. The spokesman added: The Greek positions on Skopje are well known, specific, firm, and clear. Referring to the recent violations of national airspace by Turkish aircraft, Venizelos said that the neighboring country has circles of the political and military leadership who cultivate a sense of tension.
